* phase-6 part-3b: entry/symbol definitions.
* ENTDEF exports MAIN as an entry point (-> EDEF; first ENTDEF also names the
* object unit, with PRI=1).  SYMDEF exports KOUNT (an absolute EQU -> SDEF
* constant form) and BUF (a section-relative label -> SDEF address form).  The
* names go in the DNAM record; each EDEF/SDEF entry points at its name by word
* displacement.
       ENTDEF MAIN
       SYMDEF KOUNT,BUF
KOUNT  EQU   5
MAIN   LDA   BUF
       TRA   MAIN
BUF    BSS   KOUNT
       END   MAIN
